			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The promise of digital advertising has always been measurability, but as the consumer devices that connect with world to the Internet have fragmented the promise is going unfulfilled.&nbsp; Tapad is building products that allow marketers to execute and understand their campaigns across this complex ecosystem, returning to the promise and exceeding it.&nbsp; As the Director, Product Marketing you will work closely with our product management and sales teams to tell the Tapad story to the market.&nbsp; You will need to be technical, creative, analytical, and have a passion for our customers.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Coordinate end-to-end marketing life cycle for new product releases and feature enhancements</li>
<li>
Develop customer case studies that highlight current product capabilities for use in sales process</li>
<li>
Collaborate cross-functionally with product management and sales to eliminate any gaps in product messaging</li>
<li>
As the organization grows, building out a team to meet the demand of a quickly evolving product</li>
<li>
Create sales presentations to highlight product capabilities across different use cases, verticals, and functional areas</li>
<li>
Innovate in the area of product packaging and pricing</li>
<li>
Measure customer satisfaction and present results as an actionable plan back to business stakeholders</li>
<li>
Work with corporate marketing on press opportunities and event coordination</li>
<li>
Coordinate with product management on developing friendly view of twelve month product roadmap</li>
<li>
Build out whitepapers that solidify our position as leaders in the cross-platform space</li>
<li>
Create one-sheeters for products</li>
<li>
Position Tapad and its products as core to mobile and cross-platform digital marketing</li>
<li>
Be responsible for positioning of external metrics that are shared with PR</li>
<li>
Lead go-to-market on new products with sales, account, and product teams<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
