<strong>About the Role:</strong></p>
<p>
Tapad is looking for a well-rounded Frontend Engineer who is passionate about delivering snappy, well designed, intuitive interfaces using modern frontend development libraries and frameworks. You won&rsquo;t find design-by-committee or folks handing you specs to implement at Tapad. Our frontend developers take the lead in assessing our user&rsquo;s needs, identifying the right tools, and developing creative solutions that enable colleagues and clients to interact with massive datasets and manage advertising campaigns on a complex system.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Collaborate with Product and Account Teams to iteratively design and develop intuitive interfaces, workflows and visualizations to bring simplicity to the management of a complex, dynamic adserving platform</li>
<li>
Research and experiment with libraries and frameworks to find the best components to make a growing javascript codebase easy to manage and a joy to work with.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
3+ years of experience developing large web applications in Javascript, particularly with modern MVC, MVVM Frameworks</li>
<li>
Experience with cross browser compatibility concerns</li>
<li>
Familiarity with RESTful backend development, full-stack experience a plus</li>
<li>
As passionate about code quality as about creating great U/X and highly-functional designs</li>
<li>
Outstanding communications and collaboration skills</li>
<li>
Ability to present voluminous, complex data sets intuitively to users</li>
<li>
BS or higher in Computer Science or related field preferred</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Tools We Use:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
HTML5</li>
<li>
CSS3 using LESS pre-compilation</li>
