<p>
<strong>Position Summary:</strong></p>
<p>
Interprets and ensures compliance with financial and accounting concepts, provides corporate analysis, interpretation and oversight over financial results by performing the following duties:</p>
<p>
<strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</strong> includes the following while other duties may be assigned:</p>
<p>
&bull; Analyze financial information to determine present and predict future financial performance, including trend analysis<br />
&bull; Assist the financial team in the development of budgets, planning, and other corporate financial requirements and prepare management, financial and budget submissions<br />
&bull; Review of monthly management packs for all operating units<br />
&bull; Interact with personnel from each product group monthly and during the budget process to gather and review data to produce documents and reports for management use<br />
&bull; Review of interim and year-end financial reporting packs and prepare financial statements and footnotes for stand-alone entities<br />
&bull; Review acquisition proposals submitted by operating entities; track requests and approvals - interfacing with all levels as appropriate<br />
&bull; Review and analyze capital expenditure proposals and liaise with operating units; track requests, approvals and prepare monthly reporting to parent, interfacing with all levels as appropriate<br />
&bull; Conduct specific analysis as requested and prepare reports of findings and recommendations that support financial planning and profit improvement</p>
